Package: plotcli
Title: Command Line Interface Plotting
Version: 0.2.0
Date: 2025-11-27
Authors@R: c(person("Claas", "Heuer", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "claasheuer@gmail.com"))
Description: The 'plotcli' package provides terminal-based plotting in R.
             It supports colored scatter plots, line plots, bar plots, histograms, 
             density plots, and more. The package includes 'ggplotcli2', a universal 
             converter that renders any 'ggplot2' plot in the terminal using Unicode 
             Braille characters or ASCII. Features include faceting support, automatic 
             theme detection, and multiple canvas types.
License: LGPL-3
URL: https://github.com/cheuerde/plotcli
Encoding: UTF-8
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Depends: R6, ggplot2
Imports: crayon, stringr, rlang, grDevices, stats
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
NeedsCompilation: yes
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Config/testthat/edition: 3
